<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Lots of ideas on this</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 9:01 p.m. 9/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Lots of ideas on this<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=470" TARGET=_self>Can You Say EQ: Arena</A> (ZKHades)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>I have lots of ideas on how to use the EQ Arena's, many of them I have posted in the past. For now I don't want to delve into them until we fix some more basic problems as they would be considered enhancements. Suffice it to say I think using and improving the Arena's is an excellent idea, if not just for the geographical advantages they provide. Some geographical focal points for PvP are needed, especially on the non-PvP server where it will be difficult to find others who are red, of similar level, and willing to fight.
<P>&gt; Ok this is for use after the horrendus level power differences
<BR>&gt; are fixed.
<P>&gt; I really like the idea of a place where duels could take place.
<BR>&gt; For instance an Arena where different EQ combatants could battle
<BR>&gt; it out despite the switch. A wager could even be set--for
<BR>&gt; instance two different duelist could say "Hey we have a
<BR>&gt; problem here--lets go duke it out, If i win i get your longsword
<BR>&gt; if you win i get your chainmail." Another interesting
<BR>&gt; option would be Contest s where (with different level divisions)
<BR>&gt; awards could be given like at a Tae Kwon Do tournament--White
<BR>&gt; Belts fight White Belts and Black Belts fight Black Belts. What
<BR>&gt; do ya'll think????
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
